    <subfield code="y">00000 \footnotesize (Color online) Experimental multiplicity distributions vs isotope mass, A, for the $^{64}$Ni projectile with different targets. Targets are indicated on the right for each distribution. Each data point represent summed multiplicity over Z for a give A. Solid lines are the resuts of power law fits for $1 \le A \le 30$ and dotted lines are for $10 &lt; A \le 30$. The extracted $\tau$ values are also given as $\tau_{a}$ and $\tau_{b}$, respectively.</subfield>
